  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-07-31", 
    "text": "Amends the Three Strikes and You're Out statute (providing mandatory life imprisonment of individuals who commit more than two serious violent felonies or serious drug offenses) to provide that an individual who is adjudicated a juvenile delinquent for conduct that would be considered a serious violent felony or a serious drug offense if committed by an adult shall be deemed to be convicted of such felony or offense, but only with respect to one such adjudication."
  }, 
